description.narrative: Capacity of Government is improved to implement a national urban sanitation strategy to generate demand and facilitate supply, which contributes to Sanitation, Sanitation (Covid). UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Public Engagement, Developing And Leveraging Resources And Partnerships, Evaluations, Research And Data, Fostering Innovation And Use Of New Technologies, Harnessing Power Of Business And Markets, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: More children and their families have access to basic sanitation, supported by more effective national strategies

description.narrative: The strategic investments made in urban sanitation sector by developing tools, training manuals, guidelines and their modeling during the last two years is now fruiting results. A total of 79,986 people gained access to basic sanitation 2019, resulting a cumulative total of 23,018 accessing toilets (138,108 people) against the target of 21,000. Adapting RSMS in urban context, capacity of municipal government partners enhanced in implementing social norms campaigns, technical capacity to support local artisans, and help setup small business to those eager to engage in sanitation entrepreneurship, has strengthened urban sector in three municipalities where sanitation is being modeled. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:20/12/2019
